<div class="fr-view Kanit panel-content-htmleditor"><div class="fr-view Kanit panel-content-htmleditor"><p><strong>MANUFACTURING INNOVATION SEMINAR 2019</strong></p><p><strong>USING 3D DATA</strong></p><p><br></p><p><img width="452" height="102" src="/_content_html_editor_upload/images/6F2CA4BD-1464-62B0-2E2A-2E02FE7592C9.jpeg" class="fr-fic fr-dii">      <img width="265" height="52" src="/_content_html_editor_upload/images/70766485-4EA9-58A4-63DD-E9D71A8C990B.png" class="fr-fic fr-dii"></p><p><br></p><p><strong>The first time of cooperating seminar between UEL Thailand and Yonezawa !</strong></p><p>The Manufacturing Innovation Seminar 2019 is helded on Friday 13th December 2019, for introducing an example of improving business processes from 2D (drawing) to 3D using CAD (CADmeister) and viewer (3DTascalX). We would deeply appreciate your kind assistance and would hereby like to express our thanks to more than 50 attendees to join in our seminar.</p><p>Seminar topic about : </p><p>3D data design review & measurement method for Plastic parts and Press parts. (3D Tascal)</p><p>Introduce 3D die design function for Press die and Mold die. (CADmeister)</p><p>Case study Drawing-less using 3D data for machining and inspecting process.</p><p>Basic operation experience to overview 3D data viewing, measurement, cross section, 2D drawing, sub-coordinate creation, etc.</p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><strong><img width="602" height="330" src="/_content_html_editor_upload/images/9BD5B5F9-A5F2-C53F-1C49-16BBCC7D324F.jpeg" class="fr-fic fr-dii">     <img width="602" height="451" src="/_content_html_editor_upload/images/2745D06A-507F-0C6A-B186-99F484BDC608.jpeg" class="fr-fic fr-dii">    </strong><img width="602" height="451" src="/_content_html_editor_upload/images/5E46762B-3832-A938-37D1-A062A66413EC.jpeg" class="fr-fic fr-dii"></p><p><strong><img width="602" height="451" src="/_content_html_editor_upload/images/89055D94-2AC5-7190-65C2-AA39A13C3AA2.jpeg" class="fr-fic fr-d